story: My name is Dr. Emily Martinez, and I’m 36 years old, originally hailing from Albuquerque, New Mexico, where the rich cultural tapestry of the Southwest has influenced my worldview. A pivotal moment in my life was volunteering in a mental health facility, which solidified my commitment to this field. My circle of friends is diverse and supportive, and I cherish our regular gatherings over homemade meals. I currently share my home with a spirited golden retriever named Max, who brings joy to my daily routine, which revolves around work, self-care, and nurturing relationships. While I’ve traveled throughout North America, I dream of visiting Europe to dive deeper into the cultures I’ve long admired. In my downtime, I find inspiration in podcasts and documentaries, and ultimately, I aspire to continue making a difference in the lives of my clients, promoting mental health awareness and understanding in my community.
